#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:1
msgid "Doctest Formatting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:3
msgid ""
"While _Black_ makes some decisions about styling for docstrings, it does not "
"make any assumptions about the contents of documentation. Thus, executable "
"Python code inside docstrings or documentation files (e.g. doctests), will "
"not be formatted by _Black_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:7
msgid ""
"Listed below are tools that apply _Black_ formatting to code inside "
"docstrings and documentation files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:10
msgid ""
"Note: There are some observed inconsistencies between the below packages. "
"Because of this, we hesitate to make any recommendations. Any installed "
"packages are installed at your own risk. We also encourage anyone to "
"contribute documentation for additional packages that apply _Black_ "
"formatting to doctests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:15
msgid "blacken-docs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:17
msgid ""
"[`blacken-docs`](https://pypi.org/project/blacken-docs/) is primarily used "
"to apply _Black_ formatting to code in documentation files (e.g. `.rst`, `."
"md`, `.tex`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:20
msgid "`blacken-docs` supports the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:22
msgid ""
"Python code blocks in Markdown, reStructuredText, and LaTeX files. Similar "
"to `blackdoc`, normal _Black_ formatting is applied, so doctests inside "
"Python code blocks will not be formatted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:26
#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:93
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"print(\"Hello world!\")\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:32
#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:99
msgid ""
".. code-block:: python\n"
"    print(\"Hello world!\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:37
msgid ""
"\\begin{minted}{python}\n"
"print(\"Hello world!\")\n"
"\\end{minted}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:43
msgid ""
"Doctests inside Pycon code blocks in Markdown and reStructuredText. The code "
"blocks may be included in a `.md` or `.rst` file, or inside a docstring in a "
"Python file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:46
msgid ""
"```python\n"
">>> print(\"Hello world!\")\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:52
msgid ""
".. code-block:: pycon\n"
"    >>> print(\"Hello world!\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:57
msgid ""
"def add_one(n: int) -> int:\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    Examples\n"
"    --------\n"
"    ```pycon\n"
"    >>> add_one(1) == 2\n"
"    ```\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    return n + 1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:69
msgid "blackdoc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:71
msgid ""
"[`blackdoc`](https://pypi.org/project/blackdoc/) is primarily used to apply "
"_Black_ formatting to doctests in Python files. It will not format any file "
"contents that are otherwise covered by _Black_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:75
msgid "`blackdoc` supports the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:77
msgid "Doctests in Python files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:79
msgid ""
"def add_one(n: int) -> int:\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    Examples\n"
"    --------\n"
"    >>> add_one(1) == 2\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    return n + 1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/doctest_formatting.md:89
msgid ""
"Python code blocks in Markdown or reStructuredText files. In these cases, "
"normal _Black_ formatting is applied, i.e., doctests inside Python code "
"blocks will not be formatted."
msgstr ""
